      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Commercial CFD solver with documented verification test suite and version-controlled simulation scripts; solver release notes confirm bug-fix history relevant to rotating machinery.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent 2022R2 was used with a documented QA plan including regression tests for rotating reference frame and species transport. Version control of all case files maintained in institutional GitLab repository. Achieved Gradation 2 satisfies MRL 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver passes published benchmark problems for incompressible rotating flow; order-of-accuracy confirmed for momentum and scalar transport equations.",
      "rationale": "ANSYS Fluent has been verified against lid-driven cavity and Taylor-Couette benchmarks. Internal verification reports confirm second-order spatial accuracy for the pressure-velocity coupling scheme used. Meets Gradation 2 for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study with at least three systematically refined meshes; GCI < 5% for hemolysis index QoI.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels (2.1M, 5.8M, 14.2M cells) were evaluated using Richardson extrapolation. GCI for normalized hemolysis index was 2.3% between fine and medium meshes. Achieved Gradation 3 exceeds the Gradation 2 requirement, providing additional confidence margin."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) documented and replicated in simulation within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump experimental conditions (3500 RPM, 4.0 L/min design point; four off-design points) were reproduced in CFD with inlet velocity profiles derived from upstream piping geometry. Blood analog fluid properties matched to within 2% of reported experimental values."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or normalized RMS error) defined and computed for primary QoI; comparison includes uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Normalized hemolysis index predictions agreed with experimental measurements within 18% across all five operating points, consistent with reported inter-laboratory variability in FDA pump studies. Pressure-head curve error was below 5% across the CPB envelope."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (hemolysis index, shear stress distribution, pressure head) are directly linked to the clinical decision question of worst-case hemolysis identification.",
      "rationale": "The normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and modified index of hemolysis (MIH) are the regulatory-accepted metrics for CPB device hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance. Shear stress scalar fields are the mechanistic input to the power-law hemolysis model. QoI relevance is fully established."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments conducted on the same FDA generic pump geometry under overlapping operating conditions; fluid is blood analog with documented rheological similarity.",
      "rationale": "Validation data sourced from the FDA interlaboratory study using the identical pump geometry (STL files publicly available). Operating conditions span the CPB clinical range. Blood analog (glycerol-water, 40% hematocrit equivalent viscosity) used in experiments matches simulation fluid model assumptions."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; solver error subsumed within code verification activities.",
      "rationale": "At Model Risk Level 2, explicit numerical solver error quantification beyond code verification is not mandated. Iterative convergence to residuals below 1e-5 for all equations was confirmed, providing baseline confidence without formal error bounding."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; simulation team holds relevant CFD expertise and followed documented simulation protocol.",
      "rationale": "The simulation team comprises engineers with >5 years CFD experience in cardiovascular applications. A documented simulation protocol with peer review was followed. Formal use-error analysis is not required at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 4."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; turbulence model selection and hemolysis constitutive model are documented with literature justification.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published CFD benchmarks for centrifugal pump internal flows. Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model applied per established literature. Model form uncertainty quantification beyond literature justification is scoped out at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; input parameters documented with nominal values and sources.",
      "rationale": "All model inputs (fluid viscosity, density, hemolysis model constants, rotational speed, flow boundary conditions) are tabulated with sources. Sensitivity analysis is not required at MRL 2 but is planned for future MRL 3 assessment."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
