    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out per ASME V&V 40 Table 4 for MRL 2. The CFD model is accepted as credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump in CPB applications. This assessment supports pre-market submission for a Class II CPB device. The assessment team notes that the prose description of intended use (Class II CPB device, adult patients, flow 2–6 L/min, speed 2000–4000 RPM) is embedded in the claim and requirement bindings; the structured context-of-use object is not separately encoded in this Minimal-profile package.",
